org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: In the Matter of the Application of Jung Ham and Seid Yam for Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the United States District Court
The President of the United States of America,
To Henry M. White, U.S. Commissioner of Immigration, Seattle, Washington,

We Command You, that you have the bodyies of Jung Ham and Seid Yam by you imprisoned and detained, as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Jung Ham and Seid Yam shall be called or charged, before the Hon Jeremiah Neterer United States District Judge for the Western District of Washington, at the Court Room of said Court in the City of Seattle in the Northern Division of said District of Washington, on the 6th day of December A.D. 189 1920, at two o'clock in the after noon, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said Jung Ham and Seid Yam
And have you then and there this writ.

WITNESS the Hon C.H. HanfordJeremiah Neterer, Judge of the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, this 3rd day of December in the year of our Lord one thousand eightnine hundred and twenty
